Indian Oil Said to Buy Nigerian Qua Iboe, EA Crude From Shell

-- B y   S h e r r y   S u   a n d   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-08-08T09:24:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/indian-oil-said-to-buy-nigerian-qua-iboe-ea-crude-from-shell.html
Indian Oil Corp., the nation’s
largest refiner, bought 1 million barrels each of Nigerian Qua
Iboe and EA crude from  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA)  through a tender,
according to four people who participate in the market.  The two cargoes will be loaded in the second half of
September or October, said the people who declined to be
identified because they aren’t authorized to speak to the media.  Last month, Indian Oil bought a total of 4 million barrels
of Nigerian crude for loading from late August to September.  Details of the purchase are as follows:  To contact the reporters on this story:
